1. Process, Creativity and Quality
2. The very first thing you need to learn is EVERYTHING!
3. Process is simpky the steps you use to crreate something.
4. Creativty is simply how you generate and implement ideas.
5. Quality is simply how you make sure those implementations arent junk.
6. Your goal when going through the book is not just to whip up a few copies of some Unix tools. Your goal is to use these small Unix tool projects to focus on aspects of your ability to work on larger projects.
7. Focus not on how good you are at something, but how much you improve. 
